<p><b>What is 7cs of communication with examples pdf?</b> The seven C's of communication is a list of principles for written and spoken communications to ensure that they are effective. The seven C's are: clear, correct, complete, concrete, concise, considered and courteous. You can learn more broadly about communication in our podcast on the subject.</p>
<p><b>What is the 7 rule in communication?</b> The 7-38-55 Rule indicates that only 7% of all communication is done through verbal communication, the words we speak, whereas the nonverbal component of our daily communication, such as the tonality of our voice, make up 38% and 55% from the speaker's body language and facial expressions.</p>
